Benchmark suite: hafod vs scsh

Each benchmark exists as a hafod version (*-hafod.ss) and a scsh version
(*-scsh.scm).  Thread benchmarks (09-12) are hafod-only.

Methodology:
  - Each benchmark runs 7 times; both best and median are reported
  - Timing is external (Perl Time::HiRes)
  - Ratio < 1.0 means hafod is faster; > 1.0 means scsh is faster

Requirements:
  - hafod (this repo, built via `make`)
  - scsh built from https://github.com/scheme/scsh at /tmp/scsh-master
  - A POSIX system with /etc/passwd

Setup:
  # Build hafod
  make

  # Build scsh (one-time)
  cd /tmp
  git clone https://github.com/scheme/scsh scsh-master
  cd scsh-master
  git submodule update --init
  autoreconf
  ./configure
  make

Usage:
  # Run full comparison suite:
  perl bench/run-benchmarks.pl

  # Run a single benchmark:
  time hafod -s bench/01-fork-exec-hafod.ss
  time /tmp/scsh-master/go -s bench/01-fork-exec-scsh.scm

Benchmarks:

  Part 1: hafod vs scsh comparisons

  01-fork-exec        Fork/exec/wait throughput: run (true) x 500
  02-pipeline         Pipeline throughput: (pipe (cat /etc/passwd) (wc -l)) x 100
  03-string-io        String I/O: run/string (echo ...) x 500
  04-regex            SRE regex compile + match x 10,000
  05-file-ops         File create/stat/delete cycle x 500
  06-computation      Pure Scheme computation (no POSIX) x 1
  07-env-ops          Environment variable get/set x 10,000
  08-glob             Glob /etc/* x 100
  13-startup          Startup time: import (hafod) and exit
  14-readline         Read-line throughput: read /etc/passwd x 500
  15-field-split      Field splitter: infix-splitter on colon-delimited line x 5,000
  16-awk              AWK macro: process /etc/passwd x 200
  17-regex-subst      Regex substitution: regexp-substitute/global x 5,000
  18-redir            Output capture: run/string (echo hello) x 500
  19-temp-file        Temp file create + delete x 200
  20-with-cwd         Dynamic scoping: (with-cwd "/tmp" (cwd)) x 5,000

  Part 2: hafod-only (no scsh equivalent)

  09-threads          Spawn + join 10,000 green threads
  10-channel          Channel send/receive 50,000 messages (buffered)
  11-thread-preempt   100 preemptive threads x 10,000 work units
  12-thread-ring      50-thread ring, 5,000 message passes
